1. AI Tools Utilized
ChatGPT (OpenAI): Used for structural planning, high-fidelity copywriting, and visual prompt engineering.

Stitch (Google Labs): Used for rapid UI generation, component layout, and creating the initial design system (colours, typography, and spacing).

2. Workflow and Order of Operations
Phase 1: Structure & Copy (ChatGPT)
I began by feeding the customer requirements into ChatGPT to generate a cohesive "Content Map." Since the client provided no text, I used the AI to draft professional, legal-focused headlines and service descriptions that resonate with the Russian water-use market.

Prompt: I copied and pasted from the task given

Phase 2: Visual Concept & UI Generation (Stitch)
Once the content was ready, I moved to stitch to generate the actual UI. I used a "Prompt-to-UI" approach to ensure the layout followed modern landing page conventions (Hero -> Services -> Social Proof -> Conversion).

Prompt: "Design a modern, professional marketing website for a legal company that specializes in helping businesses and individuals obtain water-use permits across Russia.

Style:

- Clean, corporate, trustworthy

- Minimalist layout with strong typography

- Blue, white, and neutral colour palette (water + legal theme)

- Use modern UI/UX practices similar to top law firm websites

- Desktop-first design (1440px width)



Structure:



1. Header

- Logo (left)

- Navigation: About, Services, Cases, FAQ, Contacts

- Right side: address (Moscow, Russia), phone number, WhatsApp/Telegram icons



2. Hero Section

- Full-width background image (river, water infrastructure, or industrial water use)

- Title: focus on water-use permits and legal services

- Subtitle: emphasize nationwide coverage across Russia

- CTA button: “Get Consultation”

- Scroll-down indicator



3. Services Section

- Grid of 4–6 service cards

- Each card includes icon, title, short description, and a “Contact via Messenger” button



4. How We Work

- Horizontal 5-step process:

  1. Free consultation

  2. Case analysis

  3. Document preparation

  4. Submission to authorities

  5. Approval and registration



5. About Company

- Two-column layout

- Left: company description

- Right: CEO photo, name, role

- Include key statistics (projects per year, approval rate, active clients)

- Add a video preview block



6. Projects / Cases

- Scrollable horizontal cards

- Each card includes:

  - Image

  - Location

  - Type of work

  - Type of document

- Clicking a card opens an image gallery



7. Testimonials

- Auto-scrolling carousel

- Client reviews with names, companies, and 5-star ratings

- Pause animation on hover



8. Rent Calculator Section

- Input fields:

  - Length (meters)

  - Width (meters)

  - Term (years)

- “Calculate” button

- Show success and error states

- Include privacy policy and consent checkbox



9. FAQ Section

- Accordion-style expandable questions

- Below it, a consultation form:

  - Name

  - Phone

  - Email

  - Submit button



10. Footer

- Logo

- Navigation links

- Address and phone

- Social media icons



Other requirements:

- Use realistic placeholder content

- Include image placeholders where needed

- Keep spacing consistent and clean

- Use modern UI components and cards"

Phase 3: Refinement & Asset Integration (Stitch)
I used stitch’s internal tools to swap out placeholder images for industry-relevant visuals (dams, riverbanks, and professional legal consultations) and refined the "Client Feedback" carousel to ensure high contrast for readability.

3. Key Features Implemented
Dynamic Hero Section: Integrated a clear Value Proposition with a high-resolution background representing the industry.

Interactive Calculator: Designed a visually distinct dark-mode block for the "Riverbank Lease Calculator" to drive user engagement.

Trust Signals: Included a "Protocol of Engagement" section and a "Case Studies" grid to satisfy the requirement for showing past work.

Conversion Optimization: Strategically placed "Request Legal Consultation" forms in the footer and FAQ sections.

